					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">On the NES, it is common to use one of the bits in PPUMASK (monochrome, color emphasis, left-edge clipping) to mark where processing for the frame is done.<br /><br />On the SNES ... it looks like you should be able to use the brightness control in <a href="http://wiki.superfamicom.org/snes/show/Registers#inidisp__screen_display_7" class="postlink">INIDISP</a> for the same effect. (I'm certain there are many options, that's just the first one that looks suitable)</div>

